column4: hey guys... what does this mean:   Depends: kdelibs4c2 but it is not going to be installed
it means that you have a dependency conflict
Thank you.  Do you know how to resolve it?
or rather how I can fix it... :)
have you mixed your repositories? It's very hard to solve circular dependencies most of the time
what do you mean by mixing them?
I went through the sourceo-matic to create my repos
the sources in your sources.list file
the places you download your programs from
here i'll copy and paste it in the pastebin .. just a sec
actually it's installing something right now so hold on a minute... ok?
wow GoDawgs I have to say that with that many sources there is no way to know where the conflict introduced itself.
so just start deleting and see what happens?
what I mean is: one program is dependent on one file that another program won't tolerate etc, etc.
I'm surprised you say that's a lot of sources... I understand many people have up to 50-75
